<h3>Question 2</h3>
<div><p><p>What do you mean by unification and lifting ? Convert following sentences into FOPL</p>
<p>Sushma likes all kinds of  practical courses.</p>
<p>AI and DBMS are practical courses.</p>
<p>Any subject anyone practices is practical course.</p>
<p>Ruby practices PHP.</p>
<p>Rita practices everything that Ruby practices.</p>
<p>Using resolution check whether “Sushma likes PHP” is inferred or not.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Unification</strong> is a process of making two different logical atomic expressions identical by finding a substitution. Unification depends on the substitution process.</p>
<p>It takes two literals as input and makes them identical using substitution.</p>
<p>Let Ψ<sub>1</sub> and Ψ<sub>2</sub> be two atomic sentences and 𝜎 be a unifier such that, <em>Ψ<sub>1</sub>𝜎 = Ψ<sub>2</sub>𝜎,</em> then it can be expressed as <em>UNIFY(Ψ<sub>1</sub>, Ψ<sub>2</sub>).</em></p>
<p>Example: Find the MGU for Unify{King(x), King(John)}</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em><strong>Numerical part:</strong></em></span></p>
<p><strong>Step 1: Let&#8217;s convert the given facts into FOPL.</strong></p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>Sushma likes all kinds of  practical courses.                                                                                                                                   ∀x likes( sushma, x) Λ practical courses(x)</li>
<li>AI and DBMS are practical courses.                                                                                                                                                  practical courses(AI)  Λ  practical courses(DBMS)</li>
<li>Any subject anyone practices is practical course.                                                                                                                           ∀y practices(y, subject)  →  practical course(subject)</li>
<li>Ruby practices PHP.                                                                                                                                                                            practices(Ruby, PHP)</li>
<li>Rita practices everything that Ruby practices.                                                                                                                               ∀x practices(Rita, x) →  practices(Ruby, x)</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Step 2: Let&#8217;s convert the FOPL to CNF.</strong></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Remove implication →</em></span></p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>∀x ( likes( sushma, x) Λ practical courses(x))</li>
<li>∀x practical courses(x)  Λ  practical coursesx)</li>
<li> ∀y,∀x ¬ practices(y, x) ∨ practical course(x)</li>
<li>∀x practices(Ruby, x)</li>
<li> ∀x ¬ practices(Rita, x) ∨  practices(Ruby, x)</li>
</ol>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>CNF of the FOPL is as:</em></span></p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>∀x ( likes( sushma, x) Λ practical courses(x))</li>
<li>∀x practical courses(x)  Λ  practical coursesx)</li>
<li> ∀y,∀x ¬ practices(y, x) ∨ practical course(x)</li>
<li>∀x practices(Ruby, x)</li>
<li> ∀x ¬ practices(Rita, x) ∨  practices(Ruby, x)</li>
</ol>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Remove quantifiers and converting it to casual form</em></span></p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li>likes( sushma, x) Λ practical courses(x)</li>
<li>practical courses(x)  Λ  practical coursesx)</li>
<li>¬ practices(y, x) ∨ practical course(x)</li>
<li>practices(Ruby, x)</li>
<li> ¬ practices(Rita, x) ∨  practices(Ruby, x)</li>
</ol>
<p>for the resolution check of &#8220;Sushma likes PHP&#8221;</p>
<p>FOPL of the given resolution is</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>likes( sushma, x)</li>
</ul>
<p>writing its contradiction as</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>¬ likes( sushma, x)</li>
</ul>
<p>now,</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-36190 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/resolution.drawio.png?resize=683%2C333&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="683" height="333"></p>
<p>since, it is not NIL so this proves that it is inferred.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
