<h2>SECTION B: Attempt any EIGHT question.</h2><h3>Question 4</h3>
<div><p><p>How can  you define AI from the dimension of behavioural process? When a machine is said to pass Turing Test?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>If a system can inherit the behavioural process of human and act rationally then it is considered as AI. The Turing Test is a method of inquiry in Artificial Intelligence (AI) for determining whether or not a system is capable of behaving like a human being. The test is named after Alan Turing, the founder of the Turing Test and an English computer scientist, cryptanalyst, mathematician, and theoretical biologist.</p>
<p>Similarly, acting rationally is also a method to determine whether the system can behave rationally or not i.e whether the system is capable of  performing task by providing a rational logic for its action that ir performed. A rational agent always behave according to the situation and decide an action always with a reasonable and sensible logic behind them. If the system can behave like human and they can provide reasoning for their actions with some logic then they can be considered as Artificial Intelligence (AI).</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em><strong>Other part:</strong></em></span></p>
<p>The Turing Test is a method for determining whether or not a system is capable of thinking like a human. According to this kind of test, a system is deemed to have artificial intelligence if it can mimic human responses under specific conditions.There are two rooms, A and B. One of the rooms contains a computer. The other contains a human. The interrogator is outside and does not know which one is a system. He can ask questions through a teletype and receives answers from both A and B. The interrogator needs to identify whether A or B are humans. To pass the Turing test, the machine has to fool the interrogator into believing that it is human.</p>
<p>To pass a Turing test, a system must have the following capabilities:</p>
<p><strong>❑ Natural Language Processing:</strong><br />
The system must be able to communicate with humans innatural language or say human understandable language successfully. Usually English is considered as natural language.</p>
<p><strong>❑ Knowledge representation:</strong><br />
System must store the data specified to different domains. It should not only be able to store them but also should know to draw useful infoemation and present them in correct mannar.</p>
<p><strong>❑ Automated reasoning:</strong><br />
System should be capable of giving a logical reason to the the problem it encounter based on the information or knowledge stored in it using some patterns.</p>
<p><strong>❑ Machine learning:</strong><br />
It should be capable of learning from the problems and can use this learning further in some other similar problem as a refrence.</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 5</h3>
<div><p><p>What is an agent ? How utility agent works? Give an example of utility agent.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>An agent is something that can receive or percept input from the environment and based on some algorith decides an action which are performed by the actuator on the environment. Agents are awear of their environment through sensors and act upon the envoronment through actuators or effectors.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone wp-image-35922" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/AGENT.drawio.png?resize=242%2C167&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="242" height="167"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">     fig: Agent</p>
<p>The agents which are developed having their end uses as building blocks are called utility-based agents. They are capable of distinguishing among the possible states on the basis of some utility function to select a goal state. These agents are similar to the goal-based agent but provide an extra component of utility measurement which makes them different by providing a measure of success at a given state. Utility describes how <em>“happy” </em>the agent is. Because of the uncertainty in the world, a utility agent chooses the action that maximizes the expected utility.</p>
<p>Some of its features are:</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>It is useful when there are multiple possible alternatives to the goal state.</li>
<li>It is quite complex.</li>
<li>It focus on the goal whose associated degree if happiness is high.</li>
</ul>
