<h3>Question 8</h3>
<div><p><p>Discuss how genetic algorithm works?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong> Genetic Algorithms(GAs)</strong> use different operations that either enhance or replace the population to give an improved fit solution. They are adaptive heuristic search algorithms that belong to the larger part of evolutionary algorithms. Genetic algorithms are based on the ideas of natural selection and genetics.</p>
<p>It basically involves five phases to solve the complex optimization problems, which are given as below:</p>
<ul class="points">
<li>Initialization</li>
<li>Fitness Assignment</li>
<li>Selection</li>
<li>Crossover</li>
<li>Mutation</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Initialization:</strong></p>
<p>The process of a genetic algorithm starts by generating the set of individuals, which is called population. An individual contains or is characterized by a set of parameters called Genes.  One of the most popular techniques for initialization is the use of random binary strings.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone  wp-image-35972" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/individual.drawio-1.png?resize=472%2C203&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="472" height="203"></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Fitness Assignment :</strong></p>
<p>It is a function which determine whether the individual is fit or not.The fitness function provides a fitness score to each individual which determines the probability of being selected for reproduction.</p>
<p><strong>Selection:</strong></p>
<p>Selection is the process of choosing individuals from the current population to become parents for the next generation. It is a critical step because it determines which individuals contribute their genetic material to the next generation.</p>
<p>The selection process is typically biased toward choosing individuals with higher fitness scores. In a maximization problem, higher fitness means a higher chance of being selected.</p>
<p><strong>Crossover:</strong></p>
<p>Crossover is the genetic operation responsible for combining the genetic material of two parent individuals to create one or more offspring. It simulates the process of genetic recombination in sexual reproduction.</p>
<p>The result of crossover is one or more offspring solutions that inherit genetic material from both parents. The hope is that this process will produce offspring with favorable combinations of genetic traits.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone  wp-image-35973" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/crossover.drawio.png?resize=252%2C173&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="252" height="173"></p>
<p><strong>Mutation:</strong></p>
<p>Mutation is a genetic operation that introduces small, random changes to the genetic material of an individual. It is used to maintain genetic diversity within the population and explore new regions of the search space. While crossover combines genetic material from two parents, mutation introduces novelty independently. It allows the genetic algorithm to escape local optima and explore a wider range of potential solutions.</p>
</div>
